22 SECTION 1.9. G.S. 90-210.127 reads as rewritten:
23 "§ 90-210.127. Record keeping.
24 (a) The crematory licensee shall furnish to the person who delivers such human remains
25 to the crematory licensee a receipt, signed by both the crematory licensee and the person who
26 delivers the human remains, showing the date and time of the delivery; the type of casket or
27 cremation container that was delivered; the name of the person from whom the human remains
28 were received and the name of the funeral establishment or other entity with whom such person
29 is affiliated; the name of the person who received the human remains on behalf of the crematory
30 licensee; and the name of the decedent. The crematory licensee shall retain a copy of this receipt
31 in its permanent records for three years.
32 (b) Upon its release of cremated reduced human remains, the crematory licensee shall
33 furnish to the person who receives such cremated those reduced human remains from the
34 crematory licensee a receipt, signed by both the crematory licensee and the person who receives
35 the cremated reduced human remains, showing the date and time of the release; the name of the
36 person to whom the cremated reduced human remains were released and the name of the funeral
37 establishment, cemetery, or other entity with whom such person is affiliated; the name of the
38 person who released the cremated reduced human remains on behalf of the crematory licensee;
39 and the name of the decedent. The crematory shall retain a copy of this receipt in its permanent
