21 threatened, the court shall issue an order restraining and enjoining the violations, and this relief
22 may be granted regardless of whether criminal prosecution is instituted under the provisions of
23 this subsection. The venue for actions brought under this subsection shall be the superior court
24 of (i) any county in which the acts are alleged to have been committed or in committed, (ii) the
25 county where the defendant in the action resides.resides, or (iii) Wake County. The Board shall
26 be entitled to reimbursement of costs and attorneys' fees expended from any defendant found to
27 have engaged in the unlicensed practice of funeral service by a court of this State."
